Cape Town - A 28-year-old man was arresting in an operaton to tackle the lucrative market of abalone trade in the Western Cape. "On Sunday 2017-08-28 at about 16:15 members of Operation Combat and the Department of Agriculture, Forest and Fisheries were busy with a crime intelligence driven operation in Marine Drive, Hawston," police spokesperson FC van Wyk said. "On arrival in Marine Drive, the members spotted the white Toyota Hilux LDV with Reg CA 654 720, standing in the bushes. As the members got closer to the vehicle, they noticed a man busy offloading bags from the vehicle. When the man saw the marked police vehicles he tried to run away but officials were able to apprehend him." While inspecting the bag the suspect left behind, the police discovered it was filled with abalone. "Fourteen bags were found on the scene it’s estimated to have a street value of R900 000." The suspect was arrested for being in possession of abalone and appeared in the Hermanus Magistrates Court on Tuesday. Cape Argus